@ThinkingandTinkering I explained  my thought  poorly but my thinking was if you heat the room quickly  you warm up the solid objects in the room  so room temperature is less at the mercy of small drafts carrying the heat away. 

Anecdotal  evedence - not definitive - but I have noticed my large  bedroom keeps warmer for longer when heated quickly (my 1kwh fan heater(slow) vs my 5kwh?  methanol burner).

For a small well sealed room I guess a 500w convection heater would be sufficient
